text.section:
The General Assembly finds that:
homemakers have been an insufficiently recognized sector of the work force who make an invaluable contribution to the welfare of the residents of this State; and
there is an ever-increasing number of individuals in this State who:
have fulfilled a role as homemaker;
in their middle years, because of separation, divorce, or the death or disability of a family member depended on for support, are:
displaced homemakers; and
without income or with substantially reduced income;
very often are ineligible for public assistance, unemployment benefits, insurance benefits, and Social Security benefits;
have the highest unemployment rate of any sector of the work force;
face discrimination in employment because of age and the absence of any recent employment experience;
often have lost rights as beneficiaries under employers' pension and health plans and other insurance plans; and
often are unacceptable to private insurance plans because of their age.
